{#- ═══ BESPOKE MIDDLE (MD small business accountant) — full depth re-flowed into shared
    dc-system v2 components, mirroring the proven PA/NJ/IN/NY/DE small-business child. Spine
    (hero/proof/§01 in-brief/§03 aiSummary/call/intake/faq/CTA) is layout-owned (t-money).
    Bespoke sections alternate white/sand. Anchors #md-svc-smb-*. Founder-name-zero. ═══ -#}

{#- THE SHORT VERSION — speakable summary (#md-svc-smb-summary) — white -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="md-svc-smb-summary">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In one paragraph</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:24px;">The short version.</h2>
    <div class="prose speakable">
      {%- for p in summary %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- THE FINANCIAL BACKBONE — the five services (numbered lift cards, each with its cross-link) — sand -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="md-svc-smb-handle" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__t">What we handle for Maryland small businesses</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:12px;">The financial backbone, built and maintained.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 36px;max-width:62ch;">Every engagement is scoped to your business and entity, delivered in your own QuickBooks file by a named Certified ProAdvisor.</p>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for s in handle %}
      <div class="lift"><span class="lift__n">{{ s.num | safe }}</span><div><h3>{{ s.title | safe }}</h3><p>{{ s.body | safe }}</p><p style="margin-top:10px;"><a href="{{ s.href }}" style="color:var(--color-accent);font-size:14px;font-weight:600;">{{ s.cta | safe }}</a></p></div></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- HONEST SCOPE — what we do / what your CPA does (two checklist cards, role label kept) — white -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="md-svc-smb-scope">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__t">Honest scope</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:12px;">What we do &mdash; and what your CPA does.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 36px;max-width:62ch;">We&rsquo;re bookkeepers and Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisors, not a CPA or tax-prep firm. The split is clean, and we coordinate directly across it.</p>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for col in scope %}
      <div class="incl-card">
        <p class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ col.role | safe }}</p>
        <h3>{{ col.title | safe }}</h3>
        <ul class="checklist">{%- for it in col.items %}<li>{{ it | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}</ul>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- THE ADVISORY LINE — statement + body prose — sand -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="md-svc-smb-advisory" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__t">Beyond the books</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="statement">Automation handles the data entry. We handle the judgment.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in advisoryBody %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- EXPERT REVIEW — firm-level byline + standards prose + trust-row + meta — white -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="md-svc-smb-review">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__t">Page review &amp; standards</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:18px;">Reviewed by the TechBrot Certified ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    <div class="byline">
      <div class="byline__mark" aria-hidden="true" style="background:var(--color-accent);"></div>
      <div>
        <p class="byline__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline__review">TechBrot Inc. &middot; Independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose" style="margin-top:22px;">
      <p>This page reflects how TechBrot handles Maryland small-business engagements. It is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at <strong>TechBrot Inc.</strong>, a Delaware-incorporated independent ProAdvisor firm serving Maryland businesses remotely across all 23 counties and Baltimore City, and reviewed for accuracy on the bookkeeping scope, the entity-aware chart of accounts, and the Maryland references (the graduated <a href="https://www.marylandtaxes.gov/individual/income/tax-info/tax-rates.php" rel="noopener nofollow">state income tax</a>, the county piggyback <a href="https://www.marylandtaxes.gov/business/income/withholding/index.php" rel="noopener nofollow">local income tax and DC/PA/VA/WV reciprocity</a>, and the 6% sales tax with the new 3% IT/data-services rate). TechBrot keeps the books and coordinates with your CPA, who files; we do not file Maryland or federal returns, the corporate income tax, the state or local income tax, the payroll-withholding filings, the sales-tax return (including the new 3% IT/data tax), or the PTE return, and do not represent clients before the Comptroller of Maryland.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for c in reviewCreds %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ c.label }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ c.detail | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-26</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-26</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-26 &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>
